Short:        SSH2 suite, client/server, sftp
Author:       s.franke@bebbosoft.de
Uploader:     s.franke@bebbosoft.de
Architecture: m68k-amigaos
Type:         comm/net
Version:      1.43
Required:     bsdsocket.library (e.g AmiTCP)

===============================================================================
NAME

BebboSSH

BebboSSH is a portable SSH2 implementation for Amiga(68000+) and Linux(any).  

Source Code: https://franke.ms/git/bebbo/bebbossh

It requires a server that supports the included cryptographic algorithms. 
The supported cryptographic methods are
* curve25519-sha256
* curve25519-sha256@libssh.org
* ssh-ed25519
* aes128-gcm@openssh.com
* chacha20-poly1305@openssh.com
* hmac-sha2-256
* sha512
So it needs a server that supports that.

It provides the following tools and libraries:
- bebbosshd
- bebbossh
- bebboscp
- bebbosshkeygen
- libcryptossh.library
- libcryptossh.library020   (rename and use this on 68020-68040 or 68080)
- libcryptossh.library060   (rename and use this on 68060)

(libs only for the Amiga)

===============================================================================
PERFORMANCE

Also get bebboget for fast https downloads!

Example timings on an Amiga 3000:
* X25519 key pair creation: ~0.9s  
* Signature verification: ~1.2s  
Use `-v5` for DEBUG logs with timing info  

It will work on an unaccelerated Amiga but establishing the connection takes
about one minute. 

Expected SCP transfer speeds (kB/s):

            UAE-A500/68000  UAE-1200/68020  A3000/68030 V4SA/68080
------------------------------------------------------------------
AES-GCM         6.6             35.6                       317
ChaChaPoly      5.8             32.2                       351

020 version UAE-A500/68000  UAE-1200/68020  A3000/68030 V4SA/68080
------------------------------------------------------------------
AES-GCM         -               44.6                       353
ChaChaPoly      -               60.1                       396

For a good terminal experience install the terminfo `xterm-amiga` 
on the remote system! On many systems you have to copy `xterm-amiga`
as root into `/usr/share/terminfo/x`

Pimp your `.bash_profile` to set `LANG=C` since the Amiga doesn't like UTF8...
A convenient way is to add this to `.bash_profile`:
  ```
    if [ "$TERM" == "xterm-amiga" ]; then
      export LANG=C
    fi
  ```

===============================================================================
PROGRAMS

===============
   bebbossh
===============
USAGE: bebbossh [options] [user@]host[:port] [command [args...]]
    -?            display this help
    -c <file>     select the config file
                  defaults to envarc:.ssh/ssh_config
    -i <file>     select the private key file for public key authentication
                  defaults to envarc:.ssh/id_ed25519
    -L [bind_address:]port:host:hostport
                  listen at bind_address:port and forward to host:hostport
    -p <port>     connect to the host at port <port>
    -T            don't allocate a pseudo terminal
    -v <n>        set verbosity, defaults to 0 = OFF
    --ciphers <n> use the ciphers in the given order:
                  1=aes128-gcm, 2=chacha20-poly1305
                  defaults to n=21
    --noesc       don't handle ESC sequences, default is on if interactive

Open a shell on the host using your console colors and mouse.   
Or execute a command via SSH2.

===============
  bebbosshd
===============
USAGE: bebbosshd [options]
    -?            display this help
    -p <port>     use the given port <port>
    -v <n>        set verbosity, defaults to 0 = OFF

* Create the folder ENVARC:ssh
* Copy the file sshd_config to ENVARC:ssh
* Edit the file ENVARC:ssh/sshd_config at your needs
* Create an unencrypted key file and name it as in ENVARC:ssh/sshd_config 
  * e.g. ENVARC:ssh/ssh_host_ed25519_key
* Create and edit the file ENVARC:ssh/passwd
  * create entries with
    username password
  * the passwords are getting hashed on first user logon

Start bebbosshd to accept remote SSH2 connections.
* A simple terminal emulation is provided. 
  (Works now for some stuff on ApolloOS)
* You may also use sftp copy files from/to the Amiga. 
  (This should work on ApolloOS too)

===============
bebbosshkeygen
===============
USAGE: bebbosshkeygen [-f <output_keyfile>]
    -?  display this help

Create ed25519 key files.

===============
bebboscp
===============
USAGE: bebboscp [options] [source] [target]
    one of [source]/[target] must be remote, the other local
    -?            display this help
    -c <file>     select the config file
                  defaults to envarc:.ssh/ssh_config
    -i <file>     select the private key file for public key authentication
    -p <port>     connect to the host at port <port>
    -t            allocate a pseudo terminal
    -u <user>     connect as <user>
                  or use <user>@<host>:<path>
    -v <n>        set verbosity, defaults to 4 = INFO
    --ciphers <n> use the ciphers in the given order:
                  1=aes128-gcm, 2=chacha20-poly1305
                  defaults to n=21

Copy files from remote to local or from local to remote.
Wildstar pattern is supported in the last element of the source.

